## Why This Is Asked
The question probes practical CKNE deployment in a latency-sensitive, multi-tenant RTB path at scale with edge aggregation and backpressure.

## Key Concepts
- CKNE health modeling at tenant granularity
- Adaptive sampling under bursts
- Edge-based health aggregation and policy refresh
- Trace fidelity under backpressure across services
- Realistic test and validation plan

## Code Example
```javascript
// CKNE health payload example
const payload = {
  tenant_id: 't123',
  ckne_latency_ms: 12,
  ckne_error_rate: 0.001,
  ckne_throughput: 1500,
  ckne_signal: 0.4
};

// Health-to-sampling update (minutely)
function updateSamplingPolicy(minHealth) {
  // return new sampling percent in [5,60]
  return Math.max(5, Math.min(60, 5 + Math.round(minHealth * 100)));
}
```

